-- Petroleo Brasileiro, Vale, Cencosud: Latin America Equity Market Preview
-- Nathan Gill
-- 2010-06-29T08:20:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-29/petroleo-brasileiro-vale-cencosud-latin-america-equity-market-preview.html

          
          
             The following companies may have
unusual price changes today in Latin American trading. Stock
symbols are in parentheses and share prices reflect the previous
close.  
 The  MSCI Latin America Index  fell 0.3 percent to 3,863.01.
In Brazil, preferred shares usually are the most-traded class of
stock.  
 Brazil  
 Petroleo Brasileiro SA  (PETR4 BS): Brazil’s state-
controlled oil company awarded  FMC Technologies Inc. , the
Houston-based provider of subsea systems for oil and natural-gas
fields, a contract worth about $300 million to provide equipment.
Petrobras dropped 1.8 percent to 27.42 reais.  
 Vale SA  (VALE5 BZ): The world’s largest iron-ore producer
said it named  Guilherme Cavalcanti  as its chief financial
officer, replacing  Fabio Barbosa . Vale fell 2.2 percent to 41.01
reais.  
 Chile  
 Cencosud SA  (CENCOSUD CC): Chile’s biggest retailer, which
operates stores in neighboring Argentina, may climb after
Argentina’s national statistics agency Indec said yesterday May
shopping center sales by volume rose 37.4 percent. Chilean
markets were closed June 28 for a national holiday. Cencosud
rose 1.7 percent to 2,477.80 pesos on June 25.  
